summary: [c] [IV][Cert][Win8.1 64] WDDM Toaster - Invalid Param Fourth Group is failing
Description: [Detailed_Description]: Problem Description ------------------------------- WDDM Toaster - Invalid Param Fourth Group test is failing in Win8.1 64 bit on CI/SI/EG/NI System Configuration: ---------------------------------- OS Win8.1 64 bit HCK Version QFE11 CPU AMD Phenom(tm) II X6 1100T Processor ASIC CI MARS ASIC ID 6601 Chipset m5a99x-evo Driver \\hydincbt03\build\1412311900\image\15.20\15.20_BR021649 Steps for repro: ------------------------ 1. Install Windows Blue 64 Bit OS. 2. Install Display Driver specified above 3. Run the tests specified below with HCK 2.1 studio. Job ID Job Name Pass Fail 427 WDDM Bit Flip - Invalid Param Fifth Group 1 1 Expected result: ------------------------- Tests should pass without any issues. Actual Result: ---------------------- Test is failing. Note: ---------- Test passed on VI. [Detailed_Problem_Expl]: EPR #412026 - [IV][Cert][Win8.1 64] WDDM Toaster - Invalid Param Fourth Group is failing [Description] Emulating displays over MST hub and hotplugging entire hub will cuase BSOD at a relatively high frequency (1/5). [Root Cause] During interrupt handling of MST emulation, there were re-entrancy issues where MsgAuxClient interrupts were somehow ending up executing DAL internal code. [Resolution] Redirect internal DAL code execution into interrupt handler for MST Emulation rather than in MstMgrWithEmulation::ProcessDiscoveryFinished where it was originally. [Reviewed by] Jun Lei Razvan Oprea

Setup the machine with the specified OS. 2. Install latest drivers for both Intel chipset and complete build for dGPU. 3. Reboot the system when asked 4. Now try to launch any OGL app like UnigineHeaven(set Open GL mode and under high performance) 5. Or try to open any OGL samples like gears, Blobs, Blendsphere on high performance mode 6. Observe the issue. Expected: ======== Everything should launch withourt any issues Actual: ====== 1) APP CRASH with a faulty module pointing to ""atigktxx.dll"" while launching (Refer the attachments) Note: ------- >> No issue when we launch or run the app on iGPU.(Intel chipset) Regression: ========= >> FAIL with 15.20Alpha5 + PX A+I (Intel BDW + Opal XT) + WinBlue64 >> FAIL with 15.20Alpha4 + PX A+I (Intel BDW + Opal XT) + WinBlue64 >> FAIL with 15.20Alpha3 + PX A+I (Intel BDW + Opal XT) + WinBlue64 >> PASS with 15.20Alpha2 + PX A+I (Intel BDW + Opal XT) + WinBlue64 >> PASS with 15.20Alpha1 + PX A+I (Intel BDW + Opal XT) + WinBlue64 >> PASS with 15.10Alpha20 + PX A+I (Intel BDW + Opal XT) + WinBlue64 [Detailed_Problem_Expl]: - EPR is hybridgraphics only, not PX related. - rootcause: ulFamily is probably not intended to be used as vendor id despite what's said in the comment. we can't use this field to populate our devlist's vendor id field - since we know we are filling info for our hybrid discrete GPU, we'll just fill in the vendor id field instead. - fix CL#1119520 promoted to mainline 2/24/2015.

Boot the system into the required set-up as mentioned. 2. Install the driver from above path 3. After driver installation install SDK by test-set : IV_AutoN_OCL_L1 --> Install_AMD_APP_StreamSDK_3.0_Win32_64 4. After installtion of SDK run the following samples BoxFilterGL.exe and GaussianNoiseGL.exe by command "" sample -e --device gpu 5. On multiple re-runs the samples crash. Out of 5 mulitple re-runs 3 times the issue was reproduced. Expected Result : =============================================================================== No sample crash must be observed Actual Result: =============================================================================== On multiple runs the samples crash. Out of 5 multiple runs 3 times the issue is observed. The following samples fail Regression: ========= 15.30-150726n-021649E-ATI ---Fail 15.30-150716n-021649E-ATI ---Fail 15.30-150715-021649E-ATI --- Build failure 15.30-150714-021649E-ATI --- Pass logs attached at : \\hydinlogs01\logs$\HY-IN-IVT5\HY-IN-IVT5-42\IV_Run_AMD_APP_OpenCL_Samples_GPU_SDK_3.x_2.x_Win_2015-07-27-11#26#22#154 Observations: ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Observing the same failure on the following configuration: PI FIJI PRO ( 7300; winblu-64 ) Triaging: ============ Replaced atikmdag.sys file from fail driver ( 15.30-150716n-021649E-ATI ) to pass driver ( 15.30-150714-021649E-ATI ) --> Fail [Detailed_Problem_Expl]: Problem: TDR happens after triggers GFX MCBP Root cause: RB META data entry was filled with NOPs because KMD failed detect preemptible draw IB. summary: [IV_Perf][Win10-64bit] Blank screen observed during running PCmark8 (Creative3.0) subtest on CZ Board
Description: [Detailed_Description]: [IV_Perf][Win10-64bit] Blank screen observed during running PCmark8 (Creative3.0) subtest on CZ Board =========================================================================================================== Configuration ------------------ CPU: AMD FX 8800PRadeon R7, 12 compute cores4C+8G 2.10GHz OS : Win10-64bit , 10240 RTM image Chipset gardenia ASIC : FUSION CARIZO Device ID : 9874 BIOS VERSION:WGA5819N RAM: 6 GB Display: HDMI Monitor Connected Build Location : \\hydincbt03\build\1508231900\image\15.30\15.30_BR021649 Steps to reproduce: ------------------------------- - Set up the above configuration - Install the above said mainline nightly driver - Install PCmark8 thru TACC or manually Test set: NPI_Install_PCMark_8 [Ver:304] - Launch PCmark8 bench and go to Developer->Creative3.0->Select all the subtests - wait for 10-20 minutes to observed the Blank screen Expected: ---------- PCmark8->Creative3.0 should run properly with appropriate results Actual: --------- Blank screen is observed during PCmark8->creative3.0 running Regression ------------ 15.30-150823n-021649E-ATI - FAIL 15.30-150728n-021649E-ATI - PASS NOTE ===== During PCmark8->Creative3.0 running when it comes to (Video group chatv2) the blank screen is observed. [Detailed_Problem_Expl]: Please verify that the latest SystemInfo file from PCMark is installed. Latest version is: Version 4.40 | August 20, 2015 http://www.futuremark.com/support/systeminfo Change 1188018 by jlu@stg-kmd-jameslu-64 on 2015/09/04 09:06:45 EPR #425606 - [IV_Perf][Win10-64bit] Blank screen observed during running PCmark8 (Creative3.0) subtest on CZ Board [Problem/Feature Description] Blank screen observed during running PCmark8 (Creative3.0) subtest on CZ Board [Solution Description] There is VM page fault because the private VA PD is not updated in process' Page Directory due to Window 10 bug (VSO 4448217). Before Microsoft fixes it in the Windows 10 future release, KMD driver needs to workaround it. 1. Add a flag ""m_IsPrivateVaPdUpdated"" in KdProcess to track the PrivateVaPD update information. 2. During process' PD update, if ""InitialUpdate"" for PD update is set, KMD will update PrivateVa PDE and set ""m_IsPrivateVaPdUpdated"" in KdProcess. If ""InitialUpdate"" is not set for PD update, KMD driver should check ""m_IsPrivateVaPdUpdated"" in KdProcess to decide if the PrivateVa PDE should be updated. [Code Review] http://codereview/go?page=ReviewDisplay&reviewid=54360 Affected files ... //depot/stg/kmd/drivers/kmd/Doc/Workarounds/KMD Workarounds.xls#69 edit //depot/stg/kmd/drivers/kmd/inc/Workaround_types.hpp#84 edit //depot/stg/kmd/drivers/kmd/kdx/src/PagingContext.cpp#146 edit //depot/stg/kmd/drivers/kmd/kdx/src/Process.cpp#24 edit //depot/stg/kmd/drivers/kmd/kdx/src/Process.hpp#12 edit //depot/stg/kmd/drivers/kmd/kdx/src/VmPageTable.hpp#37 edit //depot/stg/kmd/drivers/kmd/src/WorkaroundManager.cpp#121 edit //depot/stg/kmd/drivers/kmd/src/WorkaroundManager.hpp#60 edit

According to the Microsoft article at https://support.microsoft.com/en-in/kb/195738, this issue is caused by the compiler exceeding the memory allocation limit.  This issue is highly intermittent and happens very infrequently.  The build servers on which this build was made has plenty of RAM to be allocated. As per the resolution suggested in the Microsoft article, CN script files/make files may possibly be updated to forcibly allocate more memory during build time.  The build team can help on testing this when the CN changes are available.
